analysis: The documents primarily concern the delegation of presidential authority to various government officials and agencies. They cover a wide range of topics, including budget and accounting procedures, strategic materials stockpiling, quarantinable communicable diseases, government patents, scientific research, immigration reform, environmental quality, federal retirement systems, federal property administration, space activities, military functions, army and air force rations, disaster relief, nuclear power facilities, economic powers, defense production, Nazi war crimes records, aviation career incentive pay, federal employees holding state offices, civil rights, foreign assistance, credit control, foreign service, garnishment of pay, and school construction. The sentiment is neutral, as they are legal and administrative directives.
title: Delegation of Authority and Amendment of Existing Orders
